<Paragraph>
Excel can manage and manipulate a large range of different kinds of data.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
This section contains samples demonstrates the usage of various features such as data validation, sorting, form controls, Ole object etc. using Essential XlsIO.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Here is a list of samples with description
</Paragraph>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Range Manipulation</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how a range of cells can be manipulated using XlsIO. This includes named ranges and range copy with and without formatting. It also details how to delete a range and apply styles to a range of cells.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Data Sorting</Bold> - This sample demonstrates the data sorting with various sorting algorithm available in Essential XlsIO.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Data Validation</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how simple data validation can be performed with only a few lines of code.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Interactive Features</Bold> - This sample demonstrates the usage interactive features such as hyperlink and comments using Essential XlsIO.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Form Controls</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to insert form controls using Essential XlsIO.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Performance</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to increase the performance of XlsIO with less time and memory consumption.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>OleObject</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to insert ole object using XlsIO.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
